cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper addresses the challenge of architecture search for deep learning models, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-categories of computer science. However, given the focus on differentiable methods and the use of gradient descent, it is most likely to be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the experiments involve image classification (cs.CV), language modeling (cs.CL), and optimization (cs.NE), which are all relevant sub-categories. Finally, the use of neural networks and deep learning techniques suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible sub-category.
